<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bodge" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bodge,</orth> evidently == <emph>to budge</emph> (cf. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.388" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 388</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 44</bibl>, and <emph>budger</emph>), to yield, to give way: <cit><quote>with this, we charged again: but, out, alas! we --d again,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 19</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>